The ironic part about this verse is I wasn’t actually in the past, I was in the future (except for the durag).

It’s easy to put some words together and rap about your gun/ talk about how you gon’ blast while all your enemies run/ but be the same rappers talking’ indirect/ that don’t ever ever want beef when standing in thy flesh/

Photo by @shotbyerick_

node.text:
I just wanted to share this message with all my white and non black friends and allies. 
This probably still won’t make sense to some, but I’m hoping I will at least be able to bring a little bit of clarity to the hurt that a lot of black people have been feeling in this country.

And since some people love reminding us of Dr. King’s quotes: “I think America must see that riots do not develop out of thin air. Certain conditions continue to exist in our society which must be condemned as vigorously as we condemn riots.” - Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.

In the End, we will remember not the words of our enemies, but the silence of our friends. - Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

node.title: A message for our non black friends

The ironic part about this verse is I wasn’t actually in the past, I was in the future (except for the durag).

It’s easy to put some words together and rap about your gun/ talk about how you gon’ blast while all your enemies run/ but be the same rappers talking’ indirect/ that don’t ever ever want beef when standing in thy flesh/
